<h1 class="doc-page-title">COMPASS User guide</h1>
<p class="doc-page-lead">This guide provides step-by-step instructions for common tasks and user journeys in COMPASS.</p>

<h2 id="getting-started">Getting started</h2>

                <div class="alert alert-primary">
                    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> <strong>New to COMPASS?</strong> Check out our <a href="@Url.Action("GettingStarted", "Documentation")" class="alert-link">Getting started guide</a> for a comprehensive introduction to the system.</p>
                </div>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Accessing COMPASS</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to the COMPASS URL in your web browser</li>
                    <li>You'll be signed in automatically using your DfE Azure Entra ID credentials</li>
                    <li>You'll arrive at your personalised COMPASS dashboard</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> If you don't have access to COMPASS, contact your line manager or the COMPASS support team.</p>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">First-time setup</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Review your user profile by clicking the user icon in the top navigation</li>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>My settings</strong> to configure your preferences:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Select your preferred business areas (you can select multiple)</li>
                            <li>This will automatically filter RAID views to show items from those areas</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Familiarise yourself with the main navigation menu on the left sidebar</li>
                    <li>Explore the home dashboard to see items assigned to you</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="alert alert-success">
                    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> <strong>Tip:</strong> Setting your preferred business areas will automatically filter RAID index views to show items from those areas, helping you focus on what matters most to you. You can always override this filter to view all items.</p>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="navigation">Navigating COMPASS</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Main navigation</h3>
                <p>The left sidebar provides access to all major sections:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Home:</strong> Dashboard with overview and recent activity</li>
                    <li><strong>Delivery reporting:</strong> Submit and view product operational reports</li>
                    <li><strong>Enterprise reporting:</strong> Enterprise metrics and functional standards</li>
                    <li><strong>Reports:</strong> RAID reports and analysis</li>
                    <li><strong>Product governance:</strong> Products, risks, issues, milestones, and actions</li>
                    <li><strong>Administration:</strong> System settings and user management (administrators only)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Top navigation</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Home:</strong> Return to your personalised dashboard</li>
                    <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Access this documentation</li>
                    <li><strong>Help:</strong> Help resources and support information</li>
                    <li><strong>Dark mode toggle:</strong> Switch between light and dark themes</li>
                    <li><strong>User menu:</strong> Access My settings to configure preferences</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Breadcrumbs</h3>
                <p>Use the breadcrumb navigation at the top of each page to understand your location in the system and quickly navigate back to parent pages.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Using your personalised dashboard</h3>
                <p>Your dashboard is your command centre - it shows everything assigned to you in one place with powerful filtering options.</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Click <strong>Home</strong> to return to your dashboard</li>
                    <li>Use the horizontal tabs to switch between views:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Overview:</strong> Summary cards showing counts across all item types with colour-coded status indicators</li>
                            <li><strong>Products:</strong> Products where you're a contact, with RAID item counts and quick-access buttons</li>
                            <li><strong>Issues:</strong> Issues you own, with filtering by status, severity, and time period</li>
                            <li><strong>Risks:</strong> Risks you own, with filtering by status, risk score, and time period</li>
                            <li><strong>Actions:</strong> Actions assigned to you, with filtering by status, priority, and time period</li>
                            <li><strong>Milestones:</strong> Milestones you own, with progress tracking and filtering</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Use the inline filters to refine each view:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Time period:</strong> All time, overdue, due today, due this week, due this month, due next month</li>
                            <li><strong>Status:</strong> Filter by current status (context-sensitive for each item type)</li>
                            <li><strong>Priority/Severity:</strong> Filter by priority level or severity</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click on any item to view details or edit directly from the dashboard</li>
                    <li>Look for visual indicators:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Red badges:</strong> Overdue items requiring immediate attention</li>
                            <li><strong>Amber badges:</strong> Urgent items due within 7 days</li>
                            <li><strong>Progress bars:</strong> Visual tracking for milestones</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ol>

                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Badge counts in tabs show overdue items in red and total counts to help you prioritise your work. Make checking your dashboard part of your daily routine!</p>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="risks">Managing risks</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Creating a risk</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Risks</strong> in the sidebar menu</li>
                    <li>Click the <strong>"Create new risk"</strong> button</li>
                    <li>Complete the risk form:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Title:</strong> Brief, descriptive title for the risk</li>
                            <li><strong>Description:</strong> Detailed description of the risk</li>
                            <li><strong>Product:</strong> Select the product(s) affected by this risk</li>
                            <li><strong>Risk types:</strong> Select one or more risk categories using checkboxes (strategic, operational, financial, technical, security, etc.)</li>
                            <li><strong>Risk tier:</strong> Select the appropriate governance tier (project, programme, portfolio, department, cross-government)</li>
                            <li><strong>Business area:</strong> Optionally classify by business area (loaded from FIPS CMS)</li>
                            <li><strong>Impact:</strong> Rate the potential impact (1-5, where 5 is highest) - click the info icon for guidance</li>
                            <li><strong>Likelihood:</strong> Rate the likelihood of occurrence (1-5, where 5 is highest) - click the info icon for guidance</li>
                            <li><strong>Risk owner:</strong> Start typing a name or email to search for and assign a risk owner</li>
                            <li><strong>Proximity date:</strong> When the risk is most likely to materialise</li>
                            <li><strong>Response strategy:</strong> Choose avoid, mitigate, transfer, or accept</li>
                            <li><strong>Status:</strong> Set the initial status (typically "New" or "Open")</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create"</strong> to save the risk</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="card border-primary mt-3 mb-3">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb text-warning"></i> Best practices</h4>
                        <ul class="mb-0">
                            <li>The risk score is automatically calculated as Impact × Likelihood</li>
                            <li>Use the info icons (blue info circles) next to field labels to view detailed guidance</li>
                            <li>Select multiple risk types if the risk spans different categories</li>
                            <li>Choose the risk tier based on the governance level that should oversee this risk</li>
                            <li>Use the staff autocomplete by typing at least 2 characters to search</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Using filters on risk index</h3>
                <p>The risk index has powerful filtering capabilities to help you focus on relevant risks.</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Risks</strong> in the sidebar menu</li>
                    <li>View summary cards at the top showing:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Open risks count</li>
                            <li>Closed risks count</li>
                            <li>Overdue risks count</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Use the dimension filter to view:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>All items:</strong> All risks in the system</li>
                            <li><strong>Assigned to me:</strong> Only risks you own</li>
                            <li><strong>My business area:</strong> Risks from your preferred business areas (automatically applied if you've set preferences)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Apply additional filters using the filter panel:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Business area:</strong> Select a specific business area from the dropdown</li>
                            <li><strong>Products:</strong> Multi-select filter to show risks for specific products</li>
                            <li><strong>Risk types:</strong> Filter by risk type (strategic, operational, technical, security, etc.)</li>
                            <li><strong>Risk tier:</strong> Filter by governance tier (project, programme, portfolio, department, cross-government)</li>
                            <li><strong>Status:</strong> Filter by current risk status</li>
                            <li><strong>Risk score range:</strong> Filter by minimum/maximum risk score (1-25)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Switch between <strong>Active</strong> and <strong>Closed</strong> tabs to view different risk states</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>Clear filters</strong> to reset and view all items</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="alert alert-success">
                    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> <strong>Tip:</strong> When filtering by multiple products, use the Select2 dropdown which allows you to search and select multiple items easily. Just start typing to search!</p>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Viewing and editing risks</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Risks</strong> in the sidebar menu</li>
                    <li>Use the search or filter options to find a specific risk</li>
                    <li>Click on a risk to view its details</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Edit"</strong> to modify the risk</li>
                    <li>Update the fields as needed</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Save"</strong> to save your changes</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Linking actions to risks</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open the risk you want to add actions to</li>
                    <li>Scroll to the <strong>"Actions"</strong> section</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Add action"</strong></li>
                    <li>Either create a new action or link an existing action</li>
                    <li>The action will now appear in the risk's actions list</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Closing risks</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open the risk you want to close</li>
                    <li>Update the status to "Closed"</li>
                    <li>Add a closure note explaining why the risk is being closed</li>
                    <li>Save the changes</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="issues">Managing issues</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Creating an issue</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Issues</strong> in the sidebar menu</li>
                    <li>Click the <strong>"Create new issue"</strong> button</li>
                    <li>Complete the issue form:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Title:</strong> Brief, descriptive title for the issue</li>
                            <li><strong>Description:</strong> Detailed description of the issue</li>
                            <li><strong>Product:</strong> Select the product(s) affected</li>
                            <li><strong>Priority:</strong> Set the priority level (low, medium, high, critical)</li>
                            <li><strong>Severity:</strong> Rate the impact of the issue</li>
                            <li><strong>Issue owner:</strong> Assign an owner responsible for resolution</li>
                            <li><strong>Status:</strong> Set the initial status (typically "Open")</li>
                            <li><strong>Target resolution date:</strong> Set when the issue should be resolved</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create"</strong> to save the issue</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Tracking issue resolution</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open the issue you're working on</li>
                    <li>Update the status as work progresses (Open → In Progress → Resolved → Closed)</li>
                    <li>Add regular updates in the notes section</li>
                    <li>Link related actions that contribute to resolution</li>
                    <li>When resolved, update the status and add resolution details</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="actions">Managing actions</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Creating an action</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Actions</strong> in the sidebar menu</li>
                    <li>Click the <strong>"Create new action"</strong> button</li>
                    <li>Complete the action form:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Title:</strong> Clear, actionable title</li>
                            <li><strong>Description:</strong> Detailed description of what needs to be done</li>
                            <li><strong>Action owner:</strong> Assign the person responsible</li>
                            <li><strong>Action source:</strong> Select the source (risk, issue, meeting, decision, etc.)</li>
                            <li><strong>Due date:</strong> Set when the action should be completed</li>
                            <li><strong>Status:</strong> Set the initial status (typically "Not started")</li>
                            <li><strong>Priority:</strong> Set the priority level</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Optionally link the action to related risks, issues, or milestones</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create"</strong> to save the action</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Updating action status</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Actions</strong></li>
                    <li>Click on the action to open it</li>
                    <li>Update the status (Not started → In progress → Complete)</li>
                    <li>Add progress notes as needed</li>
                    <li>If the action is complete, add completion notes</li>
                    <li>Save your changes</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Viewing your actions</h3>
                <p>To see all actions assigned to you:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Actions</strong></li>
                    <li>Use the dimension filter to select "Assigned to me"</li>
                    <li>Apply additional filters as needed:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Action source:</strong> Filter by where the action came from (risk, issue, milestone, service assessment)</li>
                            <li><strong>Priority:</strong> Filter by priority level (high, medium, low)</li>
                            <li><strong>Status:</strong> Filter by current status</li>
                            <li><strong>Business area:</strong> Filter by business area</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Sort by due date to prioritise your work</li>
                    <li>Look for overdue indicators (shown in red) and urgent items due within 7 days (shown in amber)</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> The "Assigned to me" filter is a quick way to see all actions you're responsible for, regardless of product or business area.</p>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="milestones">Tracking milestones</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Creating a milestone</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Milestones</strong> in the sidebar menu</li>
                    <li>Click the <strong>"Create new milestone"</strong> button</li>
                    <li>Complete the milestone form:
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Title:</strong> Clear milestone name</li>
                            <li><strong>Description:</strong> What the milestone represents</li>
                            <li><strong>Product:</strong> Select the associated product</li>
                            <li><strong>Target date:</strong> When the milestone should be achieved</li>
                            <li><strong>Status:</strong> Set the current status (Not started, In progress, Achieved, etc.)</li>
                            <li><strong>Milestone owner:</strong> Assign a responsible person</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Create"</strong> to save the milestone</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Linking RAID items to milestones</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open the milestone</li>
                    <li>Navigate to the relevant section (Risks, Issues, or Actions)</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Link existing"</strong> or <strong>"Create new"</strong></li>
                    <li>Select or create the item to link</li>
                    <li>The linked items will appear in the milestone view</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="metrics">Submitting performance metrics</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Product performance metrics</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Delivery reporting → Operational reports</strong></li>
                    <li>Select your product from the list</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Submit metrics"</strong></li>
                    <li>Enter values for each metric:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Actual value (numbers, decimals, or percentages as appropriate)</li>
                            <li>Target value (if applicable)</li>
                            <li>Reporting period</li>
                            <li>Notes or commentary</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Submit"</strong> to save the metrics</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Enterprise metrics</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Enterprise reporting → Enterprise metrics</strong></li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Submit metrics"</strong></li>
                    <li>Complete the enterprise metrics form</li>
                    <li>Add any relevant notes or context</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Submit"</strong> to save</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Viewing metric history</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to the relevant metrics page</li>
                    <li>Select your product or metric</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"View history"</strong></li>
                    <li>View the trend chart and historical data table</li>
                    <li>Use filters to adjust the time period shown</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="assessments">Conducting functional standards assessments</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Starting an assessment</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Enterprise reporting → Functional standards</strong></li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Conduct assessment"</strong></li>
                    <li>Select the product being assessed</li>
                    <li>Select the functional standard to assess against</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Begin assessment"</strong></li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Completing the assessment</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Review each criterion in the selected standard</li>
                    <li>For each criterion:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Read the criterion description</li>
                            <li>Select a compliance level (Not met, Partially met, Fully met)</li>
                            <li>Provide evidence of compliance</li>
                            <li>Add notes or explanations</li>
                            <li>Attach supporting documentation if needed</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Review your assessment</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Submit assessment"</strong> to save</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Viewing assessment history</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Functional standards</strong></li>
                    <li>Select a product</li>
                    <li>View the list of completed assessments</li>
                    <li>Click on an assessment to view details</li>
                    <li>Compare assessments over time to track compliance improvements</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="reports">Viewing reports</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Risks and issues report</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Reports → Risks and issues</strong></li>
                    <li>Use the filters to refine the report:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Filter by product</li>
                            <li>Filter by status</li>
                            <li>Filter by date range</li>
                            <li>Filter by owner</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Sort columns by clicking the column headers</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>"Export"</strong> to download the report</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Analysis report</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Reports → Analysis</strong></li>
                    <li>View visual analysis of RAID data</li>
                    <li>Explore charts showing:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Risk distribution by type</li>
                            <li>Issue status breakdown</li>
                            <li>Action completion rates</li>
                            <li>Trend analysis over time</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Use filters to adjust the analysis scope</li>
                    <li>Export charts and data as needed</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Product dashboard</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to <strong>Products</strong></li>
                    <li>Select a product from the list</li>
                    <li>View the comprehensive product dashboard showing:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Product information and status</li>
                            <li>Active RAID items</li>
                            <li>Recent metrics submissions</li>
                            <li>Functional standards assessments</li>
                            <li>Upcoming milestones</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Click on any section to view more details</li>
                </ol>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="preferences">Managing your preferences</h2>
                
                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Setting preferred business areas</h3>
                <p>Configure which business areas you work with to automatically filter views to show the most relevant items.</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Click the <strong>user icon</strong> in the top navigation bar</li>
                    <li>Select <strong>My settings</strong> from the dropdown menu</li>
                    <li>You'll see a list of all available business areas (loaded from FIPS CMS)</li>
                    <li>Check the boxes next to your preferred business areas (you can select multiple)</li>
                    <li>Click <strong>Save preferences</strong></li>
                    <li>You'll see a confirmation message</li>
                </ol>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">How preferences affect your views</h3>
                <p>When you set preferred business areas:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>RAID index pages (Risks, Issues, Actions, Milestones) automatically filter to show items from those areas</li>
                    <li>You'll see a blue info banner at the top of filtered views indicating the preference filter is applied</li>
                    <li>The dimension filter will default to "My business area" when viewing RAID lists</li>
                    <li>You can easily override by selecting "All items" or a different business area from the dimension filter</li>
                    <li>Items assigned to you always appear in "Assigned to me" views regardless of business area</li>
                    <li>Your dashboard always shows your items, regardless of business area preferences</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Your preferences help you focus on relevant items without manually filtering each time. You can change them at any time in My settings, and the changes take effect immediately.</p>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Using the staff autocomplete</h3>
                <p>When assigning owners or contacts, COMPASS provides intelligent autocomplete to help you find staff quickly.</p>
                
                <h4 class="h6 mt-3">How to use it:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li>Click on any owner or assigned-to field in a form</li>
                    <li>Start typing a name or email address (minimum 2 characters)</li>
                    <li>A dropdown will appear showing matching staff members</li>
                    <li>Each result shows:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Staff member's name (prominently displayed)</li>
                            <li>Email address</li>
                            <li>Job title (if available)</li>
                            <li>Department (if available)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Use arrow keys to navigate the results or click to select</li>
                    <li>Press Enter or click on a result to select that person</li>
                    <li>Click the X button to clear your selection</li>
                </ol>

                <div class="card border-primary mt-3">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb text-warning"></i> Staff autocomplete tips</h4>
                        <ul class="mb-0">
                            <li>Search by first name, last name, or email address</li>
                            <li>You don't need to type the full name - just enough to identify the person</li>
                            <li>The search is debounced, so it won't search until you stop typing briefly</li>
                            <li>Results are limited to 20 people to keep searches fast</li>
                            <li>The feature works with keyboard navigation for accessibility</li>
                            <li>If the API is unavailable, you can still select from existing users in the database</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr class="my-4">

                <h2 id="filtering">Advanced filtering and classification</h2>

                <p>COMPASS provides powerful filtering capabilities across all RAID item types to help you focus on what matters most.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Understanding dimension filters</h3>
                <p>Dimension filters appear at the top of all RAID index pages and provide quick access to common views:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>All items:</strong> Shows all items in the system (no filtering applied)</li>
                    <li><strong>Assigned to me:</strong> Shows only items you own or are assigned to</li>
                    <li><strong>My business area:</strong> Shows items from your preferred business areas (if you've set preferences)</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="alert alert-info">
                    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> When viewing "My business area", you'll see a blue banner at the top indicating the filter is active. You can click "View all items" in the banner to temporarily override your preferences.</p>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Using summary cards</h3>
                <p>Each RAID index page displays summary cards at the top showing key counts:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Open/Active count:</strong> Number of currently active items</li>
                    <li><strong>Closed count:</strong> Number of closed or completed items</li>
                    <li><strong>Overdue count:</strong> Number of items past their due date (shown in red)</li>
                </ul>

                <p>These cards update dynamically based on your current filters.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Multi-select product filtering</h3>
                <p>When filtering by products, COMPASS uses an enhanced Select2 dropdown that supports:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Type to search:</strong> Start typing a product name or FIPS ID</li>
                    <li><strong>Multiple selection:</strong> Select as many products as needed</li>
                    <li><strong>Clear all:</strong> Click the X to remove all selections</li>
                    <li><strong>Keyboard navigation:</strong> Use arrow keys and Enter to select</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Understanding risk classification</h3>
                <p>Risks can be classified across multiple dimensions for powerful filtering and reporting:</p>

                <div class="row mt-3">
                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="h6">Risk types (multi-select)</h4>
                                <p class="small">Select one or more types that apply:</p>
                                <ul class="small mb-0">
                                    <li>Strategy risk</li>
                                    <li>Governance risk</li>
                                    <li>Operations risk</li>
                                    <li>Legal risk</li>
                                    <li>Financial risk</li>
                                    <li>Commercial risk</li>
                                    <li>People risk</li>
                                    <li>Technology risk</li>
                                    <li>Information risk</li>
                                    <li>Security risk</li>
                                    <li>Project/Programme risk</li>
                                    <li>Reputational risk</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="h6">Risk tiers (single-select)</h4>
                                <p class="small">Select the governance level:</p>
                                <ul class="small mb-0">
                                    <li><strong>Project-level:</strong> Tactical risks affecting single projects</li>
                                    <li><strong>Programme-level:</strong> Risks affecting multiple related projects</li>
                                    <li><strong>Portfolio-level:</strong> Risks affecting multiple programmes</li>
                                    <li><strong>Department-level:</strong> Risks affecting departmental objectives</li>
                                    <li><strong>Cross-government:</strong> Systemic risks affecting multiple departments</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Understanding action sources</h3>
                <p>Actions can be categorised by their source to track where work is coming from:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Risk:</strong> Actions created to mitigate or respond to risks</li>
                    <li><strong>Issue:</strong> Actions created to resolve issues</li>
                    <li><strong>Milestone:</strong> Actions created to deliver milestones</li>
                    <li><strong>Service Assessment:</strong> Actions from external reviews or third-party recommendations</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="card border-success mt-3">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <h4 class="h6"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb text-warning"></i> Classification tips</h4>
                        <ul class="mb-0">
                            <li>Use multiple risk types when a risk spans categories (e.g., both "Technology" and "Security")</li>
                            <li>Choose the risk tier based on who should have oversight, not just impact</li>
                            <li>Always specify the action source to track where work originates</li>
                            <li>Use business area classification consistently across your team</li>
                            <li>Rich classification enables better reporting and analysis</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Using tabbed views</h3>
                <p>Most RAID index pages have separate tabs for different states:</p>

                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Active/Open tab:</strong> Shows current items requiring attention</li>
                    <li><strong>Closed tab:</strong> Shows completed or cancelled items (useful for reporting and history)</li>
                </ul>

                <p>Filters apply independently to each tab, and counts are shown in the tab labels.</p>

                <h3 class="h5 mt-4">Clearing filters</h3>
                <p>When you have filters applied, a "Clear filters" button appears. Click it to reset all filters and view everything.</p>

                <div class="alert alert-success">
                    <p class="mb-0"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> <strong>Pro tip:</strong> Use filters to create focused views, then bookmark the URL. The filter parameters are included in the URL, so bookmarks will preserve your filter settings!</p>
                </div>

